1 A RESOLUTION honoring the Louisville Academy of Music for winning the
2 Governor's Award in the Arts for Education.
3 WHEREAS, the Louisville Academy of Music was founded in 1954 by Robert
4 French, offering vocal and instrumental lessons in an apartment on Bardstown Road; and
5 WHEREAS, in 1957, the Academy moved to South Fifth Street, and then into the
6 home of philanthropist James Breckinridge Speed on West Ornsby Avenue, where
7 enrollment peaked at 450 students; and
8 WHEREAS, Robert French founded the Louisville Youth Orchestra, which
9 accomplished significant growth and became a vital member of the Louisville art
10 community; and
11 WHEREAS, Robert French's wife, Ruth, has remained connected to the Louisville
12 Academy of Music with unwavering commitment through education and endowment;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, Ruth French's dedication to music education and her profound
15 influence on her students have left an indelible mark on the community; and
16 WHEREAS, over the past 64 years the Louisville Academy of Music has educated
17 approximately 11,000 students while performing with prestigious musical ensembles,
18 including the New York Philharmonic; and
19 WHEREAS, the Louisville Academy of Music annually teaches more than 600
20 students and reaches over 5,000 individuals through community programs; and
21 WHEREAS, students learn the importance of persistence toward long-term goals,
22 improved focus, and resilience, and the academic programs are accessible to all through
23 financial aid, off-site residences, and community partnerships; and
24 WHEREAS, in November 2024, the Louisville Academy of Music won the
25 Governor's Award in the Arts for Education;
26 NOW, THEREFORE,
27 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
